id: pm-qpfv
title: "Sentry PM-CLI-2C: classify Node MaxListeners runtime warnings as warning-level diagnostics"
description: Classify Node runtime warnings captured by captureConsoleIntegration at capture time so system-only handled diagnostics stay observable without becoming release-blocking error groups.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[4]: agent-ux,reliability,sentry,telemetry
created_at: "2026-07-17T13:42:02.502Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-17T15:21:10.519Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-17T13:49:19.954Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: Known Node runtime warning envelopes are downgraded to warning severity at Sentry capture time; unrelated console errors remain error-level; PM-CLI-2C is documented and no longer blocks the release reliability gate; focused and full coverage remain 100/100/100/100
parent: pm-5oj5
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Classified exact Node MaxListeners console envelopes as warning diagnostics at Sentry capture time while preserving unrelated errors.
expected_result: Handled Node runtime diagnostics remain visible in Sentry without blocking daily release health as high-severity product failures.
actual_result: Strict live Sentry gate reports critical=0 and high=0 after resolving PM-CLI-2C; focused and full exact coverage pass.
affected_version: 2026.7.17
fixed_version: next-release
component: observability/sentry-capture
regression: false
customer_impact: Prevents a non-product runtime warning from halting automated releases while retaining diagnostic visibility.
