comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-17T13:42:02.502Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check: all-status searches for PM-CLI-2C, MaxListenersExceededWarning, Socket listeners, and Sentry runtime warning severity found no canonical item. Live Sentry event e5bd8887fae0472883916b4548f890fe shows three handled system-only Node warnings at 2026-07-17T11:19:46Z, with fuzz breadcrumbs and no in-app frames; related capture policy is pm-c8qa and fuzzing program is pm-0yi7."
  "2026-07-17T13:43:29.194Z",codex-root,"TDD evidence: reproduced the release-gate blocker as a failing beforeSend regression, then classified the exact Node MaxListenersExceededWarning console envelope as warning severity with pm.diagnostic_class=node_runtime_warning. Existing tags are preserved, message and exception forms are covered, and unrelated console errors remain error-level. Focused Sentry suite passes 48/48 and ESLint passes."
  "2026-07-17T13:47:21.930Z",codex-root,"Live reliability evidence: PM-CLI-2C was resolved after root-cause capture and the strict Sentry/telemetry gate now passes with critical=0, high=0, 17 expected-handled groups, telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=0.3, and zero failures missing error_code. Full coverage passes 5,798 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; lint, zero clones, and static quality pass."
  "2026-07-17T15:21:10.519Z",codex-root,"PR #579 review round 1: corrected the canonical item title so pm-changelog describes the delivered warning-level Sentry classification rather than repeating the original high-severity defect wording."
